items.title: High-Quality Dividend Growth Near 52-Week Lows: Salesforce Is Super
5 Insightful Analyst Questions From Procter & Gamble’s Q1 Earnings Call
items.description: Procter & Gamble’s first quarter results were met with a negative market reaction, as management pointed to consumer and retail volatility in the U.S. and Europe as significant headwinds. CFO Andre Schulten explained that “the consumer has been hit with a lot, and that's a lot to process,” referencing shifting retail traffic, cautious spending, and changes in purchasing channels. Management emphasized that despite these challenges, seven out of ten product categories held or grew organic sales,
